    interestingFact: 'Despite the famous "lily of the valley" fragrance featured in dozens of perfumes (Dior\'s Diorissimo, Penhaligon\'s, etc.), the true scent of the flower is impossible to extract. The natural aroma compounds break down under any solvent extraction. Every "lily of the valley" perfume on Earth is therefore entirely synthetic — primarily a 1908 invention called hydroxycitronellal — meaning the smell most people associate with the flower is technically a 100% laboratory creation that the actual flower never produces in any bottle.',
    colors: ['White', 'Pale Pink (rare)', 'Cream'],
